-- Phillies Clinch Fourth Straight NL East Title as Roy Halladay Wins 21st
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2010-09-28T01:45:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/phillies-clinch-fourth-straight-nl-east-title-as-roy-halladay-wins-21st.html
Roy Halladay pitched a two-hitter
as the Philadelphia Phillies clinched their fourth straight
National League Eastern Division title with an 8-0 win over the
Washington Nationals.   Halladay improved his record to 21-10, becoming the first
Major League Baseball pitcher with 21 wins this season.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Erik Matuszewski at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net  